The $servers value looks like this:

mongodb://10.99.99.101:27017,mongodb://10.99.99.102:27017

These IPs are valid, and are working for many requests per second - but ~20 requests a minute are failing.

I have tried to put the FQDN of the replica set in /etc/hosts on all application and MongoDB servers. I'm confident that our DNS setup is good. The app servers are connected by gigabit network to the MongoDB servers and the network looks fine to me. There are no errors in the MongoDB server logs that I can see.

I am not sure what conditions "Name or service not known" is fired in. Does anybody have any suggestions for things to check?

